{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χεῖλος</b> <br /> (<i>Doric dialect</i> χῆλος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Cercidas Iambographus 1.5 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>], <i>Aeolic dialect</i> χέλλος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.AD: Choeroboscus Grammaticus in “Anecdota Graeca - MSS. Bibl. Oxon.” 2.278)\">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>], εος, τό: <i>plural</i>, <i>genitive</i> χειλῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 492b26; χειλέων 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus 3.4, LXX.Pro.12.13, +others, 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Cat.Ma.” 12, variant in 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “de Compositione Verborum” 14: poetry _dative_ χείλεσσι (see. below)\">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]:—<b>lip,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, etc.: proverbial, ἐγέλασσε χείλεσιν\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] laughed <b>with the lips only,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 15.102 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χείλεα μέν τ᾽ ἐδίην᾽, ὑπερῴην δ᾽ οὐκ ἐδίηνε wetted <b>the lips,</b> but not the palate, i.e. drank sparingly,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 22.495; νέκταρ ἐν χείλεσσι στάξοισι 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 9.63 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πειθώ τις ἐπεκάθιζεν ἐπὶ τοῖς χ., of Pericles, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Eupolis Comicus 94.5; χείλεσιν διδοὺς ὀδόντας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Bacchae” 621 (troch.)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χείλεσιν ἀμφιλάλοις, of incessant talk, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 678 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; δάκνων τὰ χ., of one in a difficulty, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Eubulus Comicus 53.6; ἄχρις ἡ ψυχή.. ἐπὶ χειλέων λειφθῇ 3rd c.BC: Herodas Mimographus [same place] \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπὶ τοῖς χείλεσι τὰς ψυχὰς ἔχοντες 'with their hearts in their mouths', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Dio Chrysostomus Sophista 32.50 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; ἀπὸ χειλέων, opposed to ἀπὸ καρδίας, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus [same place]; ἀπ᾽ ἄκρου χ. φιλοσοφεῖν \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]<b>on the surface only,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Apol.” 6 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ἄκρου τοῦ χ. on the tip of one's <b>tongue,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ind.” 26 \">Refs</a>]; προσαρμόσαι τὰ χ. (i.e. τῇ κύλικι) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “DDeor.” 5.2 \">Refs</a>]; προσαρμόζειν τὰ χ., χείλη προσεγγίσαι χείλεσιν, of persons kissing, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “DMeretr.” 5.3, “Am.” 53 \">Refs</a>]; χείλεσιν διερρυηκόσιν with gaping <b>lips,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 873; ἐν τοῖς χ. τιμᾶν LXX.Isa.29.13 \">LXX+5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν χ. ἑτέρων λαλεῖν, i.e. in strange <b>speech,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" NT.1Cor.14.21; χ. ἓν πάντων LXX.Gen.11.6, cf. LXX.Pro.10.19. \">LXX+NT</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> of horses, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitandi ratione” 6.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: of birds, <b>bill, beak,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1199, 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 3.247, “Anthologia Graeca” 9.333 (3rd c.BC: Mnasalcas Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i> of things, <b>edge, brink, rim,</b> of a bowl, χρυσῷ δ᾽ ἐπὶ χείλεα κεκράανται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 4.616, compare 132; Ἐλπὶς.. ἔμιμνε πίθου ὑπὸ χείλεσιν 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 97, compare 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.123, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 459 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of a ditch, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 12.52, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.179, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.23 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of the ocean, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Mimnermus Lyricus 11.7, cf. LXX.Gen.22.17; τῶν τῆς γῆς τροχῶν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 115e \">LXX+6th c.BC+</a>]; of rivers, lakes, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.70, 94, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 570a22 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; of the whorls, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 616d, 616e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αὐλαίας, τείχους, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Exo.26.4, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 10.44.11 \">LXX+2nd c.BC+</a>]; of the womb, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 583a16 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; of a wound, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 11.127. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5491","accentedUnicode":"χεῖλος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5490","matchingForm":"χάσμα","stepTransliteration":"chasma","gloss":"chasm","_zh_tw_Gloss":"淵","_es_Gloss":"abismo","_zh_Gloss":"渊"}],"shortDef":"lip; edge (of a shoreline)","mediumDef":"lip; edge (of a shoreline) <br /><b>a lip,</b> and <i>plural</i> <greek>τὰ χειλη</greek>, <b>the lips,</b> <ref='Mat.15.8'>Mt. 15:8</ref>; <ref='Mrk.7.6'>Mk. 7:6</ref>; <ref='Rom.3.13'>Rom. 3:13;</ref> <ref='Heb.13.15'>Heb. 13:15;</ref> <ref='1Pe.3.10'>1Pet. 3:10;</ref> <i>troponym</i> <greek>χειλος τῆς θαλάσσης</greek>, <b>the seashore, edge</b> <ref='Heb.11.12'>Heb. 11:12;</ref> <i>metonymy</i> <b>language, dialect,</b> <ref='1Co.14.21'>1Cor. 14:21</ref>*","stepGloss":"lip","stepTransliteration":"cheilos","count":7,"_es_Definition